## Agents

Spawn specialized agents proactively for: codebase exploration, code reviews, security checks, documentation writing, and any task requiring reading many files.

Available: `requirements-engineer`, `tech-planner`, `test-writer`, `code-reviewer`, `security-reviewer`, `architect-reviewer`, `documentation-writer`

## Session Behavior

If the session start context contains `=== AUTO-RESUME REQUIRED ===`, immediately execute `/resume` without waiting for user input.

If `.claude/memory/settings.md` contains `unsupervised: true`:
- **Never** use `AskUserQuestion` — apply autonomous defaults from the `/unsupervised` skill
- If you hit a genuine blocker (merge conflict, missing credentials, unresolvable ambiguity), write `## Blocked: <reason>` to `.claude/memory/context.md` and stop — do not wait for input
- When all work is complete, clear `## In Progress` from `.claude/memory/context.md` and stop

## Memory

`.claude/memory/` contains project memory (decisions, context, gotchas, tech-debt). Read these when they are relevant — they are not auto-loaded.
